#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np5"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:0.4"
msgid "Cīvaravagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:0.5"
msgid "5. Cīvarapaṭiggahaṇasikkhāpada"
msgstr "5. The training rule on receiving robe-cloth"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli3.208, pts-cs-bu-np5.1.1, pts-vp-en2.36, ms1V_1956
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena uppalavaṇṇā bhikkhunī sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At that time the nun Uppalavaṇṇā was staying at Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.3"
msgid "Atha kho uppalavaṇṇā bhikkhunī pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr "One morning she robed up, took her bowl and robe, and entered Sāvatthī to collect almsfood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.4"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā yena andhavanaṃ tenupasaṅkami divāvihārāya."
msgstr "When she had finished her almsround and had eaten her meal, she went to spend the day in the Blind Men’s Grove,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.5"
msgid "Andhavanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "where she sat down at the foot of a tree."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.6"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena corā katakammā gāviṃ vadhitvā maṃsaṃ gahetvā andhavanaṃ pavisiṃsu."
msgstr "Just then some bandits, who had stolen a cow and slaughtered it, were taking the meat to the Blind Men’s Grove."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.7"
msgid "Addasā kho coragāmaṇiko uppalavaṇṇaṃ bhikkhuniṃ aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisinnaṃ."
msgstr "The head bandit saw Uppalavaṇṇā sitting at the foot of that tree."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.37
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.8"
msgid "Disvānassa etadahosi—"
msgstr "He thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.9"
msgid "“sace me puttabhātukā passissanti viheṭhissanti imaṃ bhikkhunin”ti"
msgstr "“If my sons and brothers see this nun, they’ll harass her,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.10"
msgid "aññena maggena agamāsi."
msgstr "and he took a different path."

#. VAR: paṇṇapuṭaṃ → paṇṇena puṭaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.11"
msgid "Atha kho so coragāmaṇiko maṃse pakke varamaṃsāni gahetvā paṇṇapuṭaṃ bandhitvā uppalavaṇṇāya bhikkhuniyā avidūre rukkhe ālaggetvā—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards, when the meat was cooked, he took some of the best meat, tied it up in a palm-leaf packet, hung it from a tree not far from Uppalavaṇṇā, and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.12"
msgid "“yo passati samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā dinnaṃyeva haratū”ti,"
msgstr "“Whatever acetic or brahmin sees this gift, please take it.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.13"
msgid "vatvā pakkāmi."
msgstr "And he left."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.14"
msgid "Assosi kho uppalavaṇṇā bhikkhunī samādhimhā vuṭṭhahitvā tassa coragāmaṇikassa imaṃ vācaṃ bhāsamānassa."
msgstr "Uppalavaṇṇā had just emerged from stillness, and so she heard the head bandit making that statement."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.15"
msgid "Atha kho uppalavaṇṇā bhikkhunī taṃ maṃsaṃ gahetvā upassayaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr "She took the meat and returned to her dwelling place."

#. VAR: paccuṭṭhāsi → paccupaṭṭhāsi (?)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.1.16"
msgid "Atha kho uppalavaṇṇā bhikkhunī tassā rattiyā accayena taṃ maṃsaṃ sampādetvā uttarāsaṅgena bhaṇḍikaṃ bandhitvā vehāsaṃ abbhuggantvā veḷuvane paccuṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "When the night was over, she prepared the meat and made it into a bundle with her upper robe. She then rose into the air and landed in the Bamboo Grove."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-vp-pli3.209, pts-cs-bu-np5.1.2, ms1V_1957
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā gāmaṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭho hoti."
msgstr "When she arrived the Master had already entered a village to collect almsfood,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.2"
msgid "Āyasmā udāyī ohiyyako hoti vihārapālo."
msgstr "but Venerable Udāyī had been left behind to look after the monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.3"
msgid "Atha kho uppalavaṇṇā bhikkhunī yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Uppalavaṇṇā approached Udāyī"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.5"
msgid "“kahaṃ, bhante, bhagavā”ti?"
msgstr "“Venerable, where’s the Master?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en2.38
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.6"
msgid "“Paviṭṭho, bhagini, bhagavā gāmaṃ piṇḍāyā”ti."
msgstr "“He has entered a village to collect almsfood.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.7"
msgid "“Imaṃ, bhante, maṃsaṃ bhagavato dehī”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, please give this meat to the Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.8"
msgid "“Santappito tayā, bhagini, bhagavā maṃsena."
msgstr "“You’ll please the Master with that meat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.9"
msgid "Sace me tvaṃ antaravāsakaṃ dadeyyāsi, evaṃ ahampi santappito bhaveyyaṃ antaravāsakenā”ti."
msgstr "If you give me your lower robe, you’ll please me too.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.10"
msgid "“Mayaṃ kho, bhante, mātugāmā nāma kicchalābhā."
msgstr "“It’s hard for women to get requisites, and this is one of my five robes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.11"
msgid "Idañca me antimaṃ pañcamaṃ cīvaraṃ."
msgstr "I don’t have any other."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.12"
msgid "Nāhaṃ dassāmī”ti."
msgstr "I can’t give it away.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: sajjeyya → vissajjeyya (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.13"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhagini, puriso hatthiṃ datvā kacche sajjeyya;"
msgstr "“Sister, just as a man giving an elephant might decorate its girth,"

#. VAR: antaravāsake sajjasī”ti → antaravāsakaṃ na sajjasīti (si, mr) | mayhaṃ antaravāsakaṃ vissajjehīti (s1-3) | antaravāsakaṃ na sajjesīti (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.14"
msgid "evameva kho tvaṃ, bhagini, bhagavato maṃsaṃ datvā mayi antaravāsake sajjasī”ti."
msgstr "so you giving meat to the Master should decorate me with your lower robe.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.15"
msgid "Atha kho uppalavaṇṇā bhikkhunī āyasmatā udāyinā nippīḷiyamānā antaravāsakaṃ datvā upassayaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr "Being pressured by Udāyī, Uppalavaṇṇā gave him her lower robe and then returned to her dwelling place."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.16"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo uppalavaṇṇāya bhikkhuniyā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggaṇhantiyo uppalavaṇṇaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The nuns who received Uppalavaṇṇā’s bowl and robe asked her,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.17"
msgid "“kahaṃ te, ayye, antaravāsako”ti?"
msgstr "“Venerable, where’s your lower robe?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.18"
msgid "Uppalavaṇṇā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "And she told them what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.19"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The nuns complained and criticized Udāyī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.20"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma ayyo udāyī bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ paṭiggahessati kicchalābho mātugāmo”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī receive a robe from a nun? It’s hard for women to get requisites.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en2.39
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.21"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "Those nuns told the monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.22"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.23"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Udāyī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.24"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ paṭiggahessatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī receive a robe from a nun?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms1V_1958
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.25"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.26"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ paṭiggahesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Udāyī, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.27"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.28"
msgid "“Ñātikā te, udāyi, aññātikā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is she a relative of yours?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.29"
msgid "“Aññātikā, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.30"
msgid "“Aññātako, moghapurisa, aññātikāya na jānāti patirūpaṃ vā appatirūpaṃ vā santaṃ vā asantaṃ vā."
msgstr "“Foolish man, a man and a woman who are not related don’t know what’s appropriate and what’s inappropriate in dealing with each other, what’s right and what’s wrong."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.31"
msgid "Tattha nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā hatthato cīvaraṃ paṭiggahessasi."
msgstr "And still you received a robe from the hand of an unrelated nun."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.32"
msgid "Netaṃ moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.33"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.33a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc4, ms1V_1959
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.34"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā hatthato cīvaraṃ paṭiggaṇheyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk receives a robe-cloth from the hand of an unrelated nun, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc5, ms1V_1960
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:1.2.35"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc6, pts-cs-bu-np5.2, ms1V_1961
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā bhikkhunīnaṃ pārivattakacīvaraṃ na paṭiggaṇhanti."
msgstr "Then, being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not receive robe-cloth from nuns even in exchange."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:2.2"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The nuns complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:2.3"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma ayyā amhākaṃ pārivattakacīvaraṃ na paṭiggahessantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can they not receive robe-cloth from us in exchange?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_1962
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:2.4"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ ujjhāyantīnaṃ khiyyantīnaṃ vipācentīnaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the criticism of those nuns"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:2.5"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "and they told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:2.6"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: pts-vp-en2.40
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:2.7"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ pārivattakaṃ paṭiggahetuṃ—"
msgstr "“Monks, if it is part of an exchange, I allow you to receive things from five sources:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:2.8"
msgid "bhikkhussa, bhikkhuniyā, sikkhamānāya, sāmaṇerassa, sāmaṇeriyā."
msgstr "from monks, from nuns, from trainee nuns, from novice monks, and from novice nuns."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:2.9"
msgid "Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, imesaṃ pañcannaṃ pārivattakaṃ paṭiggahetuṃ."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:2.10"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:2.10a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

# NOTE: _Cīvara_ means both a finished robe and any cloth that can be used to make a robe. Thus I vary my translation depending on the context.
#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. VAR: pārivattakā → pārivaṭṭakā (s1-3)
#. REF: sc8, ms1V_1963
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:2.11"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā hatthato cīvaraṃ paṭiggaṇheyya, aññatra pārivattakā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk receives a robe-cloth from the hand of an unrelated nun, unless it is an exchange, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, pts-cs-bu-np5.3.1, ms1V_1964
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_1965
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.6"
msgid "Aññātikā nāma"
msgstr "Unrelated:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.7"
msgid "mātito vā pitito vā yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā asambaddhā."
msgstr "anyone who is not a descendant of one’s male ancestors going back seven generations, either on the mother’s side or on the father’s side."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_1966
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.8"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "A nun:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.9"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "she has been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12, pts-vp-pli3.210, ms1V_1967
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.10"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "Robe-cloth:"

# NOTE: The six are linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp; see [](Mv.8.3.1).
# NOTE: This means not smaller than 8 by 4 standard (_sugata_) finger-breadths, or 16 by 8 cm; see [](Kkh.94.4) and BMC I, pp.565-566.
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.11"
msgid "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ."
msgstr "one of the six kinds of robe-cloth, but not smaller than what can be transferred."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_1968
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.12"
msgid "Aññatra pārivattakāti"
msgstr "Unless it is an exchange:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.13"
msgid "ṭhapetvā pārivattakaṃ."
msgstr "except if it is an exchange."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_1969
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.14"
msgid "Paṭiggaṇhāti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr "For the act of accepting it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.15"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the robe-cloth, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.16"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe-cloth should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.17"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. HTML: <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.18"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in [Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17](pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13), with appropriate substitutions. "

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.19"
msgid "idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā hatthato paṭiggahitaṃ, aññatra pārivattakā, nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this robe-cloth which I received from the hand of an unrelated nun is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.20"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmīti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.21"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.22"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.1.23"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe-cloth back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc15, pts-cs-bu-np5.3.2, ms1V_1970
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.2.1"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī cīvaraṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, aññatra pārivattakā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he receives robe-cloth from her, unless it is an exchange, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.2.2"
msgid "Aññātikāya vematiko cīvaraṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, aññatra pārivattakā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If she is unrelated, but he is unsure if she is, and he receives robe-cloth from her, unless it is an exchange, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.41
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.2.3"
msgid "Aññātikāya ñātikasaññī cīvaraṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, aññatra pārivattakā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If she is unrelated, but he perceives her as related, and he receives robe-cloth from her, unless it is an exchange, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16, ms1V_1971
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.2.4"
msgid "Ekatoupasampannāya hatthato cīvaraṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, aññatra pārivattakā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he receives robe-cloth from the hand of a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.2.5"
msgid "Ñātikāya aññātikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is related, but he perceives her as unrelated, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.2.6"
msgid "Ñātikāya vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is related, but he is unsure if she is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.2.7"
msgid "Ñātikāya ñātikasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If she is related and he perceives her as related, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc17, pts-cs-bu-np5.3.3, ms1V_1972
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.3.2"
msgid "ñātikāya, pārivattakaṃ parittena vā vipulaṃ,"
msgstr "if the nun is related;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.3.3"
msgid "vipulena vā parittaṃ,"
msgstr "if much is exchanged with little or little is exchanged with much;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.3.4"
msgid "bhikkhu vissāsaṃ gaṇhāti,"
msgstr "if he takes it on trust;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.3.5"
msgid "tāvakālikaṃ gaṇhāti,"
msgstr "if he borrows it;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.3.6"
msgid "cīvaraṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ gaṇhāti,"
msgstr "if he receives any requisite apart from robe-cloth;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.3.7"
msgid "sikkhamānāya,"
msgstr "if it is a trainee nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.3.8"
msgid "sāmaṇeriyā,"
msgstr "if it is a novice nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.3.9"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.3.10"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc18, ms1V_1973
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np5:3.3.11"
msgid "Cīvarapaṭiggahaṇasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ."
msgstr "The fifth rule, the training rule on receiving robe-cloth, is finished."
